pika bundles no third-party model weights, but downloads the following at
first index when clip.enabled is set in pika.config.ts:

  Model:    Xenova/clip-vit-base-patch32 (ONNX conversion of openai/clip-vit-base-patch32)
  Revision: d15189d7028b43f1d3e65039190477f6af591c2a (pinned in lib/match/clip.ts)
  Source:   https://huggingface.co/Xenova/clip-vit-base-patch32
  Upstream: CLIP by OpenAI, https://github.com/openai/CLIP (MIT License)
  Cache:    data/models/ (gitignored, local only)

Offline installs: pre-seed the cache directory and set PIKA_ALLOW_LOCAL_MODELS=1
to let transformers.js resolve local model directories.
